
[1]pusillanimous

   PUSILLAN'IMOUS, a.

   1. Destitute of that strength and firmness of mind which constitute
   courage, bravery and fortitude; being of weak courage; mean spirited;
   cowardly; applied to persons; as a pusillanimous prince.

   2. Proceeding from weakness of mind or want of courage; feeble; as
   pusillanimous counsels.
